aa(lp64
VSo the world's first satellite, Sputnik I,
p65
aVwas launched in 1957,
p66
aVand in that year, there were only a total of three launch attempts.
p67
aVDecades later and dozens of countries from all around the world
p68
aVhave launched thousands of more satellites into orbit,
p69
aVand the frequency of launches is only going to increase in the future,
p70
aVespecially if you consider things like the possibility
p71
aVof 900-plus satellite constellations being launched.
