aa(lp95
VOf the nearly 7,000 satellites launched since the late 1950s,
p96
aVonly about one in seven is currently operational,
p97
aVand in addition to the satellites that are no longer working,
p98
aVthere's also hundreds of thousands of marble-sized debris
p99
aVand millions of paint chip-sized debris
p100
aVthat are also orbiting around the Earth.
